        "title": "fix(llm): prevent reasoning_content leak when reasoning is disabled",
        "body": "### Type of Change\r\n- [x] Bugfix\r\n\r\n### Issue / Problem Description\r\nGeneric `openai-completions` and `openai-transport-stream` multiplexers extract `reasoningFields` unconditionally, causing leaked raw internal thinking chunks to merge into the user content flow when reasoning is explicitly disabled.\r\n\r\n### Real Behavior Proof\r\n- **Expected:** `reasoning_content` omitted when reasoning is false.\r\n- **Observed:** Raw English thinking block chunks leak into visible message text.\r\n- **Fixed:** Kept `markStrict()` boundaries fully intact while wrapping output streaming logic in proper gating controls.\r\n\r\n```json\r\ndata: {\"choices\":[{\"delta\":{\"reasoning_content\":\"leaked_internal_thinking_text\",\"content\":null}}]}\r\n",
